Ten children were left injured on Wednesday morning when
the taxi they were travelling in veered off an un-named road near the
Mariannhill Cemetery in Mariannhill, KwaZulu Natal.ER24 paramedics, along with other services, arrived on
the scene to find a taxi some distance off the road down an embankment. Several
children were found walking around on the scene.ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said paramedics assessed
the patients and found that 10 children, aged between 5 and 7, had sustained
only minor injuries. Fortunately, no serious injuries or fatalities were found
